  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Rajasthan has three seasons: scorching summer (April-June, up to 50°C in the Thar), monsoon (July-September) and a glorious winter (October-March). October to March is the golden window — forts glow in winter sun, desert nights are cool and clear, and the Pushkar Camel Fair and Jaipur Literature Festival both fall in this period.</p>
